  <programme start="20251225005900 +0000" stop="20251225012900 +0000" channel="SPEEDVISION.us">
    <title>Caffeine &amp; Octane</title>
    <desc>S1 E101 Delta Wing Racer with a Vengeance
State-of-the-art engineering and passion projects take center stage on this edition of Caffeine &amp; Octane. The revolutionary Delta Wing Racer turns on hot lap after hot lap at Road Atlanta, and driver Katherine Legge offers insight on how “less is more” when it comes to power to weight ratios; the dark world of a graffiti artist paints a picture of a car called Vengeance while the hosts share the eclectic hybrids of machines that make it to Caffeine and Octane with Vengance’s creator Totem.</desc>
  </programme>
  <programme start="20251225012900 +0000" stop="20251225020000 +0000" channel="SPEEDVISION.us">
    <title>Caffeine &amp; Octane</title>
    <desc>S1 E102 Henry Ford III &amp; Counterfeit Cars
The word is out that Caffeine &amp; Octane is the ultimate scene and the place to be seen. Even after 12 hours of racing at the Petit Le Mans endurance race, Henry Ford III, the great grandson of Henry Ford the industrial magnate and current member of Ford’s Board of Directors, showed up to take in the sights, address the crowds, and sign a one of a kind Ford Shelby GT350R. The GT350R will hit the road with Operation Hope to encourage young people to study math and science through motorsports; Covert car counterfeiter, Chuck Beck looks for Ford’s approval on his own version of a muscled up Festiva. YouTuber ‘That Dude in Blue’ David Patterson joins Skip and Bryan to get a special look at the motor-based philanthropic outreach and amazing cars that come with it done by John Hope Bryant, friend of Caffeine and Octane.</desc>
  </programme>
  <programme start="20251225020000 +0000" stop="20251225022900 +0000" channel="SPEEDVISION.us">
    <title>Caffeine &amp; Octane</title>
    <desc>S1 E103 Go Fast Collections
Rickey and Bryan race outside of their comfort zones, each competing to find the raddest car collection. Rickey hangs out with classic racer, Ron Green, who shows him the ropes in the ultra light &#x27;83 Ralt RT5. Bryan visits a collection of 120 racing motorcycle owned by mechanic and racer Mike McConville. Mike takes Bryan motorcross racing in his backyard after showing off his high horsepowered car collection. Caffeine and Octane alongside Ron Green visit Atlanta&#x27;s first Concours d&#x27;elegance to look at classic cars that have been perfectly maintained for decades.</desc>
  </programme>
  <programme start="20251225022900 +0000" stop="20251225025900 +0000" channel="SPEEDVISION.us">
    <title>Caffeine &amp; Octane</title>
    <desc>S1 E104 The Wrap on the Most Beautiful Cars
Wayne Phears’ Jaguar E-Type was nothing more than a diamond in the rough before the mineral rights attorney took on the basket case. Caffeine &amp; Octane brings viewers the story of how Phears’, through relentless research and determination, restored and reunited the #10 Jag that Enzo Ferrari called “the most beautiful car ever made”; Atlanta Wraps shows how wrapping Corvettes and Lamborghinis can color a car fast. Caffeine and Exotics is featured again to show off the coolest wraps Atlanta can supply.</desc>
  </programme>
  <programme start="20251225025900 +0000" stop="20251225032900 +0000" channel="SPEEDVISION.us">
    <title>Caffeine &amp; Octane</title>
    <desc>S1 E105 Panoz Racing &amp; Chasing Chevys
Twenty-five years of hand building record-setting race cars is no easy task. But don’t tell that to Don Panoz who takes on Porsches and Ferraris with his laid back personality and a full-production facility that makes improvised versions of Americas V-8’s; Caffeine &amp; Octane gets an exclusive look at an elusive man’s life long pursuit of everything Chevrolet.</desc>
  </programme>
  <programme start="20251225032900 +0000" stop="20251225035900 +0000" channel="SPEEDVISION.us">
